    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-18T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-18T16:00:00-05:00" n="400"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d400">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 E.W./10–1844: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Alexander C. Kirk</persName>,
                        Political Adviser, Allied Force Headquarters, to the <gloss type="to"
                            >Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caserta</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-18T22:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 18, 1944—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>824. General Wilson has designated his Chief of Staff Lieutenant General J. A. H.
                    Gammell as his representative to sign Bulgarian armistice terms at Moscow. It is
                    expected that General Gammell will proceed in very near future for this purpose.
                    Major General I. H. Edwards of General Gammell’s staff will accompany General
                    Gammell to the Soviet Union with understanding that Edwards is serving on staff
                    of SACMED and not as the United States representative in connection with signing
                    of Bulgarian armistice terms.</p>
                <p>Repeated Moscow 56, sent Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
